[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] ### CSS Bug (the real issue)
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] 
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] ```
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] ```
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] **File:** `packages/ai-tutor/src/components/ChatWidget.tsx:512`
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] ### Fix Applied
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] **The FloatingTutorButton button and the chat popup shared the exact same CSS position: `bottom: 24px; right: 24px;`.** When the popup opened (380×560px at z-index 9999), it completely covered the 56×56px button (z-index 100) at the bottom-right corner. Users clicking the button perceived "nothing happened" because the button disappeared behind the popup without any visual cue of separation.
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] **The JavaScript click-handler chain is correct** — no logic bug preventing the popup from opening. The chain works as:
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] 
[2026-07-02T12:02:50.870Z] [INFO] [stdout] 
